    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>meat-free chick'n </strong>to a bowl along with your <strong>dried basil</strong> and <strong>dried oregano</strong> and mix well until evenly coated</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sun-dried-tomato-meat-free-chick-n-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated meat-free chick'n</strong> and cook for 6-7 min or until brown all over, then transfer to a plate and set aside for later</p><p>Reserve the pan</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sun-dried-tomato-meat-free-chick-n-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely dice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Return the pan to a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> and cook for 1-2 min further or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sun-dried-tomato-meat-free-chick-n-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the onion is cooking, add your <strong>pasta</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the pasta for 8-10 min or 7-9 min (10-12 min for wholewheat) until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>pasta</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sun-dried-tomato-meat-free-chick-n-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the garlic is fragrant, wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper and add to the pan along with your <strong>ground paprika</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until wilted</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sun-dried-tomato-meat-free-chick-n-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut your <strong>sun-dried tomatoes </strong>in half</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sun-dried-tomato-meat-free-chick-n-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained</strong> <strong>pasta </strong>to the pan with your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>soft cheese</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong>, <strong>cooked meat-free chick'n</strong>, <strong>halved sun-dried tomatoes </strong>and a splash of <strong>reserved</strong> <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 1 min further or until the sauce begins to stick to the pasta \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy sun-dried tomato meat-free chick'n conchiglie</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sun-dried-tomato-meat-free-chick-n-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy sun-dried tomato meat-free chick'n conchiglie</strong> and sprinkle with the <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
